) (
<bibRefCitation id="C01916F69E2AFFD4FDF5FF3DFD7D4D92" author="Wu, C." box="[527,643,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" pagination="316 - 320" refId="ref3589" refString="Wu, C. (2020) Four new species of Limacodidae from China (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea). Zoological Systematics, 45, 316 - 320." type="journal article" year="2020">Wu, 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4376B079E2AFFD4FF3DFF11FD2E4C46" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FF3DFF11FED74DF6" box="[199,297,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">Remarks</emphasis>
. An assignment of this species to 
<taxonomicName id="638810849E2AFFD4FD4BFF11FC374DF6" authority="Walker, 1865" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[689,969,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Aphendala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FD4BFF11FCD44DF6" box="[689,810,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">Aphendala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C01916F69E2AFFD4FCC9FF11FC374DF6" author="Walker, F." box="[819,969,186,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" pagination="323 - 706" refId="ref3543" refString="Walker, F. (1865) s. n. In: List of the Specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Part XXXII. Printed by order of the trustees, London, pp. 323 - 706." type="book chapter" year="1865">Walker, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
seems inappropriate according to the revised definition of the genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="C01916F69E2AFFD4FE04FF75FD424DDA" author="Solovyev, A. V." box="[510,700,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" pagination="349 - 360" refId="ref3415" refString="Solovyev, A. V. (2010) A review of the genus Aphendala Walker, 1865 with notes on confusing genera (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae). Atalanta, 41, 349 - 360." type="journal article" year="2010">Solovyev (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. In fact, it exhibits several similarities with the species of 
<taxonomicName id="638810849E2AFFD4FAB8FF75FA624DDA" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" box="[1346,1436,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Calauta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FAB8FF75FA624DDA" box="[1346,1436,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">Calauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the wing patterns and the genital characters. In the present study, the generic transfer of the species to 
<taxonomicName id="638810849E2AFFD4FAD2FEA9FA7C4C3E" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" box="[1320,1410,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Calauta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FAD2FEA9FA7C4C3E" box="[1320,1410,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">Calauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed. This is the only species of 
<taxonomicName id="638810849E2AFFD4FDC2FE8DFD6C4C62" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" box="[568,658,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Calauta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FDC2FE8DFD6C4C62" box="[568,658,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">Calauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whose both sexes are known. It is noteworthy that 
<taxonomicName id="638810849E2AFFD4FB2EFE8DFA9B4C63" authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="2020" box="[1236,1381,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Aphendala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notoseusa">
<emphasis id="96FCB7159E2AFFD4FB2EFE8DFA9B4C63" box="[1236,1381,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="444">C. notoseusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses broader forewings than the other congeners.
</paragraph>
